fields.description:
h4. Problem Description
we used xCode 3.X for some time with Ti Studio (latest), today we upgraded to xCode 4.2 on top of OSX snow leopard.

Now, we can't build anyome, any project, new or old, including Kitchen Sink results in. 

h4. Actual Results
[INFO] Detected third-party module: ti.barcode/1.7
[INFO] Detected third-party module: ti.barcode/1.7

  File "/Library/Application Support/Titanium/mobilesdk/osx/1.8.1/iphone/run.py", line 39, in run

when trying to run directly from xCode we get this error:

env: python: No such file or directory



h4. Expected Results
The machine working fine after upgrading Xcode.

comments.body:
If it doesn't work directly from Xcode, then I think this is a SDK bug.

Otherwise, based on the error you saw with "python not found", I saw something similar before. Restarting the machine fixed it.
Running this with the Mobile Team.

Hello,
Asked the customer to reinstall everything, and he still gets the issue:

completly uninstalled xCode, using special command line tool
completly uninstalled Ti Studio, by dragging it to Trash
deleted the .titanium folder
deleted the Titanium Studio Workspace folder in my home folder
cleared the trahcan
updated the system to the latest Apple updates
redownloaded copies of studio and xCode (dmg)
restarted
install xCode 4.2.1 for snow leopard
install Ti studio
updated Ti studio
updated Ti studio SDK (Downloads SDK 1.8.2)
check the Help menu and STILL see Aptana instead of studio sub menu
created a new project using the master detail template
